File: South Africa has reported 114 new deaths in the last 24-hours. JOHANNESBURG - The health department said 1,745 new COVID-19 cases have been reported. This brings the total number of infections to 676,084. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Deaths rise to 16,667 It said 132 more people have succumbed to the virus in the past 24 hours. South Africa's death toll is now 16,886. Ninety percent of the people infected with the coronavirus have recovered. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.